title: I-Team learns identities of four victims injured in shooting in Cleveland
content:
CLEVELAND– The FOX 8 I-Team has now learned the identities of the four victims injured during a mass shooting Sunday on Bosworth.
The shooting claimed the life of 47-year-old Michael Matthews. Four others, 41-year-old Ronald Dernett; 22-year-old Tunisha Jackson, who is pregnant; 24-year-old Tyshaun Jenkins; and 53-year-old Awilda Carroll, were injured.
No arrests have been made and detectives are continuing to investigate.
